---
description: Require data-testid on new interactive UI elements for agent and Playwright selectors
globs:
  - frontend/src/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# Selector conventions

Add `data-testid` to new interactive elements:

| Element | Pattern |
|---------|---------|
| Page loading/error/empty | `page-loading`, `page-error`, `page-empty` |
| Nav home | `nav-home` |
| Nav settings | `nav-settings` |
| Hero banner | `hero-banner` |
| Hero play button | `hero-play` |
| Library search input | `library-search` |
| Search results dropdown | `search-results` |
| Search result row | `search-result-{type}-{id}` |
| Settings page | `settings-page` |
| Wikipedia toggle | `settings-wikipedia-toggle` |
| Auto thumbnails toggle | `settings-auto-thumbnails-toggle` |
| Simple VLC toggle | `settings-simple-vlc-toggle` |
| VLC playback options group | `settings-vlc-options` |
| VLC subtitles toggle | `settings-vlc-subtitles-toggle` |
| VLC resume toggle | `settings-vlc-resume-toggle` |
| VLC TV playlist toggle | `settings-vlc-tv-playlist-toggle` |
| VLC playlist advance toggle | `settings-vlc-playlist-advance-toggle` |
| Scan on startup toggle | `settings-scan-on-startup-toggle` |
| Browse row random toggle | `settings-browse-row-random-toggle` |
| Settings version | `settings-version` |
| GitHub link | `settings-github-link` |
| Rescan button | `rescan-library` |
| Settings media folders list | `settings-media-folders` |
| Add movies folder | `settings-add-movies-folder` |
| Add TV folder | `settings-add-tv-folder` |
| Media root row | `settings-media-root-{index}` |
| Remove media root | `settings-remove-media-root-{index}` |
| Manual media path input | `settings-media-path-input` |
| Add manual media path | `settings-media-path-add` |
| Setup wizard | `setup-wizard` |
| Setup wizard scan | `setup-wizard-scan` |
| Browse row section | `browse-row-{slug}` |
| Browse row scroll container | `browse-row-scroll-{slug}` |
| Poster card | `poster-card-{type}-{id}` |
| Poster watch progress bar | `{cardTestId}-progress` |
| Episode play | `play-episode-{id}` |
| Up-next play | `play-up-next` |
| Mark show watched | `mark-show-watched` |
| Mark show unwatched | `mark-show-unwatched` |
| Mark season watched | `mark-season-{n}-watched` |
| Mark season unwatched | `mark-season-{n}-unwatched` |
| Watched checkbox | `watched-episode-{id}` |
| Episode currently playing | `play-episode-{id}` with `data-playing="true"` |
| Show detail page | `show-detail` |

Notes:

- `{cardTestId}` defaults to `poster-card-{type}-{id}`; movie cards with `onPlay` use the card id as the play button (no `-play` suffix).
- `{slug}` is the row identifier from the browse API (e.g. `recently-watched`, `movies-2010s`).
- `{type}` is `movie` or `show`; `{id}` is the database id.

Prefer `data-testid` over text or CSS selectors in Playwright specs.
